  <header>
    <h1>Aidentis AI Dental Diagnostics Platform</h1>
    <p>
      AI-powered dental diagnostics for modern orthodontic and imaging clinics.
      Aidentis provides instant cephalometric analysis, automated CBCT interpretation
      and interactive 3D models to improve clinical precision and patient communication.
    </p>
    <a class="btn" href="mailto:assylzat@aidentis.cc?subject=Aidentis%20Demo%20Request">Request a demo</a>
  </header>

  <section id="problem-solution">
    <h2>Why Aidentis?</h2>
    <p>
      Traditional dental imaging workflows are manual, time-consuming and prone to measurement variation.
      Aidentis automates landmark detection, measurements and volumetric analysis so clinicians can
      focus on diagnosis and treatment planning instead of repetitive tasks.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="features">
    <h2>Key capabilities</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Instant cephalometric analysis</h3>
        <p>Automatic landmark detection and measurement extraction for orthodontic cases.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>CBCT scan interpretation</h3>
        <p>AI-driven volumetric analysis and anatomical structure detection with structured reports.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>3D model generation</h3>
        <p>Generation of interactive 3D models to support treatment planning and patient education.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Patient communication</h3>
        <p>Visual explanations and simulations that help patients understand conditions and options.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="cloud">
    <h2>Built on Google Cloud</h2>
    <p>
      Aidentis uses <strong>Vertex AI</strong> for model training and deployment,
      <strong>Cloud Storage</strong> for secure imaging data handling and
      <strong>Cloud Run</strong> for scalable, container-based inference services.
      Access is protected with Cloud IAM, encrypted in transit and at rest, and designed to support
      healthcare data protection requirements in multi-clinic environments.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="workflow">
    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>
      Clinics upload lateral cephalograms or CBCT scans via a secure web interface.
      Images are preprocessed and sent to Aidentis AI models running on Google Cloud.
      The system returns cephalometric measurements, CBCT findings, and optional 3D reconstructions,
      which can be reviewed, exported as reports or used in chairside patient discussions.
    </p>
  </section>

